text: Nikolayevka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Nikolayevsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 830 as of 2010. == Geography == It is located 30 km from Sterlitamak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Nikolayevka, Nikolayevsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
